HEADWORD: Academician
<hw>Ac`a*de*mi"cian</hw> <pr>(#; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>acad⟦eacute⟧micien</ets>. See <er>Academy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A member of an academy, or society for promoting science, art, or
literature, as of the French Academy, or the Royal Academy of
arts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collegian.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>academicianship</ent>⟦br⟧
